21:13.621 --> 21:18.626
of which the U.S. was running about half. All of 
these would be more expensive than the

21:19.667 --> 21:33.903
submersible, and most oceanographers would 
gladly welcome another research ship, which

21:19.667 --> 21:33.903
could only improve the overall global capability 
by 3%. And it seemed logical that rather than

21:35.865 --> 21:40.810
building another general-purpose research 
ship, it would make more sense to build some

21:41.195 --> 21:53.550
special purpose ships that could go down to the 
bottom and look with the eyeball. And in

21:55.372 --> 22:08.147
actuality, these are really perhaps more 
comparable to the fact that the geologist has long

21:55.372 --> 22:08.147
been associated with the burrow or the mule. And we 
wanted some kind of a mule that would dive so we

22:08.347 --> 22:18.899
could go down and look over the terrain that was 
otherwise not accessible.

