29:21.529 --> 29:23.231
it is very elementary. From simple geometry, you 
can figure out what the forces are, because if you

29:24.572 --> 29:40.167
build a submarine only to go shallow, it is so thin 
that it is able to collapse in any number of funny

29:24.572 --> 29:40.167
modes, and you need complicated ribs. And this is a 
real job for the mathematical experts. However,

29:44.552 --> 29:47.755
if you decide to build a whole of a simple form, like 
a cylinder or even more so a sphere. And then you

29:52.212 --> 29:56.456
design it to go deep. The hole gets thick enough so 
it is what we call a simple, it would fail in pretty

29:56.616 --> 30:08.768
close to the pressure of simple collapse. And you 
would not have the thing going out of round and

30:09.569 --> 30:15.835
getting into mathematical complications. until 
you got almost to the ultimate point. So from this

30:20.537 --> 30:26.345
standpoint, the deeper the submarine goes, the 
easier it is to design. You choose the material on

30:28.387 --> 30:45.670
the basis of corrosion, on the basis of its 
strength-weight ratio, and on the basis of its

30:28.387 --> 30:45.670
